Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.48,0:13:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在我小时候 命令我写的\N{\r原文字幕}Me. When I was a kid.  You, uh, you dictated it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.54,0:36:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做作业,玩桌游,说真心话\N{\r原文字幕} -Yeah, homework,board games, heart-to-hearts,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.00,0:00:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何他不在时,爱会越来越深?\N{\r原文字幕}Why is love intensified  by absence?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.01,0:00:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是什么感觉?\N{\r原文字幕}How does it feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.00,0:31:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你叫什么?\N{\r原文字幕}What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.72,0:00:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么感觉啊?\N{\r原文字幕}Hmm.  How does it feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.14,0:00:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,普普通通吧\N{\r原文字幕}Normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.46,0:43:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你毫无选择的余地\N{\r原文字幕}No choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.23,0:00:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彷佛什么都没有\N{\r原文字幕}You know. Like nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.31,0:00:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彷佛你稍微神游了一下\N{\r原文字幕}Like your attention wandered  for a moment, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.48,0:00:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,突然间你读的书就不见了\N{\r原文字幕}suddenly the book you're reading  is gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.57,0:00:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,咖啡和房间都不见了\N{\r原文字幕}your coffee's gone, the room is gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.90,0:00:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,突然就掉进了水沟里\N{\r原文字幕}and you're ankle-deep  in a ditch...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.95,0:00:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是在高速公路上\N{\r原文字幕}...or in the middle  of a highway...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.62,0:00:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该死\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.12,0:00:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是在野外的牛群之中\N{\r原文字幕}...or in a field full of cows.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.67,0:00:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了,全身是赤裸的\N{\r原文字幕}And of course...  ...you're naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.22,0:00:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不只回到过去还全身赤裸\N{\r原文字幕}Back in time, and naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.35,0:01:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,床上会变得空荡荡\N{\r原文字幕}The bedsheets will go slack.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.64,0:01:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或莲蓬头的水会一直冲着  或是培根会放着继续煎\N{\r原文字幕}Or the shower will keep running,  or the bacon will keep frying,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.65,0:01:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或者会听到咖啡杯碎裂一地\N{\r原文字幕}or you'll hear  a coffee cup smash on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.73,0:01:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就知道他不见了\N{\r原文字幕}and you realize, he's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.65,0:01:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又来了\N{\r原文字幕}It's happened again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.37,0:01:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只剩下一迭衣服\N{\r原文字幕}He's just a pile of clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.17,0:01:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接着就开始了\N{\r原文字幕}And then it starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.34,0:01:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等待\N{\r原文字幕}The waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.64,0:01:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,时空旅行不是超能力\N{\r原文字幕}Time travel.  It's not a superpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.94,0:01:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是某种缺陷也是我的问题\N{\r原文字幕}It's a disability.  It's what's wrong with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.32,0:01:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我无法掌握当下而是‥\N{\r原文字幕}I can't keep hold  of the current moment, I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.28,0:02:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彷佛从手中滑落  我就回到了过去\N{\r原文字幕}slide off. I fall back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.32,0:02:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不见时我会等他也会担心\N{\r原文字幕}When he's gone,  I wait and I worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.49,0:02:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不停想他在何时何地\N{\r原文字幕}I wonder where he is,  when he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.42,0:02:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是不是有危险?\N{\r原文字幕}If he's in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.59,0:02:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时你会回到原本的位置\N{\r原文字幕}Now, sometimes you ping  straight back to where you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.09,0:02:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,读著书或喝着咖啡  然后就没事了\N{\r原文字幕}You know, to your book,  to your coffee, and it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.67,0:02:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不算什么,就像睡了五分钟\N{\r原文字幕}It's nothing.  Five minutes, a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.14,0:02:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时长达数天,数周甚至数月\N{\r原文字幕}Sometimes it's days, weeks,  months,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.02,0:02:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你得想办法活下来\N{\r原文字幕}and you have to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.19,0:02:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有三件事我变得很在行\N{\r原文字幕}Now, three things I got good at.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.40,0:02:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,逃跑,战斗和偷窃\N{\r原文字幕}Running, fighting, and stealing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.32,0:02:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些你必须都很在行\N{\r原文字幕}You have to be good at those,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.45,0:02:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毕竟无论到哪里  你都浑身赤裸\N{\r原文字幕}when wherever you go, you're naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.20,0:02:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该死\N{\r原文字幕}Fuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.13,0:03:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个问题真难回答\N{\r原文字幕}Well,  that's a difficult question.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.14,0:03:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认真在问我这个问题吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Seriously,  you're asking me that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.97,0:03:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们第一次见面是什么时候?\N{\r原文字幕}When did we first meet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.27,0:03:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一次见面?\N{\r原文字幕}First meet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.98,0:03:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你先定义"第一次"\N{\r原文字幕}Define "first."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.52,0:03:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我嫁给了一名时空旅人\N{\r原文字幕}I married a time traveler.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.98,0:03:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这可说来话长了\N{\r原文字幕} It's complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.00,0:04:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本剧中英双语字幕由 雪碧居士 制作合成 全网首发
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.74,0:04:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若你不是时空旅人\N{\r原文字幕}If you're not  a time traveler, the past
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.33,0:04:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的过去就是过去了\N{\r原文字幕}is what you're stuck with.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.04,0:04:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若你是艺术家  或认为可能是艺术家\N{\r原文字幕}If you're an artist,  or think you might be,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.87,0:04:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要创造的是未来\N{\r原文字幕}the future  is what you're gonna make.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.54,0:05:01.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时你能在一盆污水中看见未来\N{\r原文字幕}Sometimes, you can see  the future in a bowl of slop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.13,0:05:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他时候‥\N{\r原文字幕}Other times...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.93,0:05:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克蕾儿,你还好吗?\N{\r原文字幕}-Clare? You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.09,0:05:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我需要什么吗?\N{\r原文字幕}-You know what I need?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.27,0:05:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费曼博士  我得去一趟图书馆\N{\r原文字幕}Dr. Felman, I need to go  to the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.56,0:05:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-去吧  -是纽伯利图书馆\N{\r原文字幕}-Okay.  -The Newberry Library.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.98,0:05:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-那里有什么?  -色情影片\N{\r原文字幕}-What's there?  -Porn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.65,0:05:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他时候?\N{\r原文字幕}Other times...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.44,0:05:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他时候你则会记得\N{\r原文字幕}...other times, you remember
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,未来总会在你的  不意中找上门\N{\r原文字幕}that the future is just what shows up  when you're looking for something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.95,0:05:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人都认为图书馆\N{\r原文字幕}People think
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.08,0:05:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是安静的地方\N{\r原文字幕}libraries are quiet places.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.12,0:05:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对我来说图书馆彷佛是一群人\N{\r原文字幕}To me a library is a crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.50,0:05:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若你是时空旅人  过去不再只是过去\N{\r原文字幕}If you're a time traveler,  the past is alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.30,0:05:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过去正在发生而且也很危险\N{\r原文字幕}It's still happening,  still dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.92,0:05:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有书架上的书都像笼子的铁杆\N{\r原文字幕}All those books  on all those shelves are like the bars on a cage,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.55,0:05:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而里头的野兽来回踱步\N{\r原文字幕}and the beast inside is pacing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.10,0:05:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对其他人而言过去已逝\N{\r原文字幕}For everybody else,  the past is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.85,0:06:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对我来说  我仍试着在过去中活下来\N{\r原文字幕}For me, well,  I'm still trying to survive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.56,0:06:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些是你的吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Are these yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.40,0:06:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在书库中找到的\N{\r原文字幕}I found them in the stacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.11,0:06:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对,谢了\N{\r原文字幕}Uh... yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.61,0:06:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨利,我一直想问你  为什么总是四处乱丢衣服?\N{\r原文字幕}Henry. I've been meaning  to ask you. Why do you leave piles  of clothes all over the place?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.20,0:06:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-大家不都这样吗?  -才不是\N{\r原文字幕}-Doesn't everyone?  -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,情况很复杂\N{\r原文字幕}It's complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.04,0:06:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好啊,我听你说\N{\r原文字幕}Okay. I'm listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.79,0:06:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说来话长\N{\r原文字幕}-It's a long story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.21,0:06:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,时间于我不成问题\N{\r原文字幕}-Time isn't a problem for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.29,0:06:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可真幸运\N{\r原文字幕}Lucky you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.84,0:06:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨利\N{\r原文字幕}Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.34,0:06:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿\N{\r原文字幕}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.56,0:06:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不好意思  -你还好吗?\N{\r原文字幕}...the language of-- -Ah, excuse me. You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.69,0:06:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对,我很好  你们在这里做什么?\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, no, I'm good.  What's going down here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.98,0:06:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,展示稀有字典\N{\r原文字幕}Presentation  on rare dictionaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.53,0:06:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊,我很爱字典\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, God. I love dictionaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.19,0:06:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道字典最棒的是什么吗?\N{\r原文字幕}You know the best thing  about a dictionary?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.03,0:06:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯有字典才会正确顺序排列单字\N{\r原文字幕}It's the only book with words  in the right order.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.24,0:06:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们没事,谢谢你,亨利\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, we're good here.  Thanks, Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.29,0:06:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正确的顺序非常重要  相信我\N{\r原文字幕}The right order is very important. You can trust me on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.42,0:07:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,稍等片刻  迪坦布先生也许能帮上你\N{\r原文字幕}If you wait just one moment,  perhaps Mr. DeTamble can help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.96,0:07:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\N{\r原文字幕}-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.30,0:07:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伊莎贝尔\N{\r原文字幕}-Ah, Isabelle?  -Hmm?
